      "Eau Rouge–Raidillon was not taken flat by Formula 1 cars until the early 1990s, when increasing aerodynamic downforce finally made it physically possible; today every car on the grid clears it at full throttle on every lap.",
      "Michael Schumacher's Formula 1 debut — substituting for the injured Bertrand Gachot at Jordan in 1991 — took place at Spa, where he qualified seventh before a mechanical failure ended his race on lap one.",
      "Multiple tragedies have occurred at Spa across motorsport disciplines over the decades, including Formula 2 driver Anthoine Hubert's fatal accident in 2019, reminding the sport that Spa's beauty and its danger are permanently inseparable."
