    history:
      "The Autodromo Nazionale Monza opened in 1922, making it one of the oldest purpose-built racing circuits in the world still in active use. It hosted the Italian Grand Prix at the very first Formula 1 World Championship season in 1950 and has appeared on the calendar at almost every subsequent season. The circuit originally included a banked oval section used in conjunction with the road circuit until 1969, when safety concerns led to the elimination of the banking; the crumbling concrete structure can still be seen adjacent to the modern circuit as a haunting relic. In 2026, following Imola's departure from the calendar, Monza carries the full weight of Italian Formula 1 pride alone.",
