    history:
      "The Madring was announced in January 2024, when Formula 1 confirmed a long-term agreement to move the Spanish Grand Prix from Barcelona's Circuit de Catalunya to a new street-hybrid circuit in the Spanish capital from 2026. The circuit was designed by Italian circuit architect Jarno Zaffelli of the Dromo engineering firm, with construction carried out by a joint venture of Spanish company ACCIONA (60%) and French firm Eiffage Construction (40%) at a total cost of €83.2 million. FIA Grade 1 homologation was obtained ahead of the 2026 debut. The circuit surrounds and integrates with the IFEMA exhibition centre in the Barajas district near Adolfo Suárez Madrid–Barajas Airport.",
