    history:
      "The Singapore Grand Prix debuted in September 2008 as the world's first genuine Formula 1 night race. The decision to race at night was driven by a combination of European television broadcast scheduling and the practical impossibility of racing in Singapore's extreme daytime heat and humidity. The circuit has undergone modifications in 2023, with significant changes to the section around the Anderson Bridge. Singapore has consistently renewed its Formula 1 contract and has become one of the most commercially successful and visually distinctive events on the calendar.",
