      "Despite running maximum wing angles to compensate for altitude-reduced downforce, cars at Mexico City still regularly exceed 360 km/h on the main straight because the thin air reduces aerodynamic drag by as much as it reduces aerodynamic grip, producing net gains in top speed.",
      "The Foro Sol baseball stadium section holds approximately 30,000 spectators in permanent grandstands that are positioned just metres from the circuit — the noise and proximity of the crowd through this section is unlike anything at any other Formula 1 venue.",
      "Ricardo Rodríguez, one of the two brothers after whom the circuit is named, died during a non-championship qualifying session here in November 1962 at just 20 years old — one of the youngest fatalities in Formula 1 history.",
      "Since Sergio Pérez joined Red Bull Racing in 2021, tickets for the Mexican Grand Prix have sold out in hours rather than weeks, making it one of the most commercially oversubscribed events on the Formula 1 calendar.",
